## Steps

### 2018-09-26 -- Mash day

1. Collect 15 gallons [carbon-filtered](https://www.morebeer.com/products/water-filter-kit-10.html) Longmont tap water
2. Add all grains to a mesh bag and throw into kettle to create mash in with 11.3 gallons of strike water @ 152°F in kettle
3. Mash temp 150°F
4. Add 3mL of 88% lactic acid, 1.5 tsp of gypsum, 0.5 tsp CaCl2 -- mash ph 5.83.
5. Remove malt, boil 15 minutes
6. Chill to 111°F
7. Add 12mL 88% lactic acid and 4x [vanilla chamomile
   GoodBelly](https://goodbelly.com/products/vanilla-chamomile/) shots to kettle,
   cover with plastic wrap, bungee cord a hot pad to it to keep >75°F for 4 days

![Kettle wrapped with hotpad](https://photos.tylercipriani.com/thumbs/b3/1383c344650b270a408dcbbc8e1cbb/large.jpg)

### 2018-09-30 -- boiling day

1. After 4 days, boil for 90 minutes (because you did your calculations all wrong because you don't do this very much and you need to boil-off A LOT!)
2. Preboil pH: 3.54
3. 10 minute: Add 1 tsp Wyeast Brewer's Choice Nutrient
4. 2 minute: Add 1 tablet whirlfloc
5. Chill to 68°F with [hydra](https://jadedbrewing.com/products/the-hydra)
6. Collect 5.5 Gallons wort
7. Pitch with 1 pack Imperial Citrus (2018-08-09 mfg date)

### 2018-10-06 -- fruiting day

1. Add 6lbs partially thawed frozen tropical medley (strawberry, blueberry,
   mango), and 1lb frozen dragon fruit puree, this will drop temp to 57°F, panic
   briefly, shrug and walk away instead.

### 2018-10-21 -- <strike>Yak shaving</strike> Bottling day

![Finished bottle](https://photos.tylercipriani.com/thumbs/32/1318a169cb43a8a3a7ab0eda245a90/large.jpg)

1. Add 4x jars of [CK Products Super Pearl Edible Luster
   dust](https://www.amazon.com/CK-Products-Super-Luster-Dust-Edible/dp/B01HDP9QKE?th=1)
   to the keg
2. [Counter-pressure](https://www.morebeer.com/products/counter-pressure-bottle-filler.html) fill a few [Bormioli Rocco Fiaschetta bottles](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0118OJQT2/).
